Flooding at Life Private Hospital in Komani (eNCA/Screenshot) JOHANNESBURG - Patients at Life Private Hospital in Komani have been evacuated and moved to Life East London Private Hospital. The hospital was flooded following heavy rains which caused a nearby dam to overflow. The incident took place Tuesday night. READ: North West Floods | NGO steps in with aid Emergency services officials say all the patients have been evacuated and moved to safety. Pictures on social media show cars in the parking lot immersed in water. Patients at Life Private Hospital in Komani have been evacuated and moved to an East London facility. The hospital was flooded following heavy rains, which caused a nearby dam to overflow last night. Emergency services officials say all patients are safe. #DStv403 #eNCA pic.twitter.com/KD32TtaXwv